ISLAMABAD, June 12 (APP): Prime Minister Muhammad Shehbaz Sharif Sunday said that the fiscal budget 2022-23 had provided more educational opportunities for youth, particularly from Balochistan and targeted subsidies to the financially weaker segments of society.
On his Twitter handle, the prime minister said the fiscal budget also represented significant improvements in several ways. The non-productive assets of the rich were also taxed.
